The first time I stumbled onto this pizza spot was about 5 years ago. I'm from New York and I had been searching the DMV for good NYC styled pizza place for some time. This was the first place that sold pizza by the slice [not jumbo size] and had a similar cheese and thin crunchy crust like the mom and pop shops back in NYC. At the time they also sold Birch Beer which was a plus. I went back recently and they no longer sell Birch Beer, but they do have root beer. The pizza still has that thin crispy crust and stringy cheese that I like. I ordered the lunch special, which is essentially two slices and a soda for about $6 . As you can see from my pics, they didn't skim on the the extra toppings I added. My only gripe is that the toppings aren't baked in when the pizza is originally cooked. Instead, the pizza is reheated with the toppings added on top. [Just a for warning for those who may care about that sort of thing.] With that aside, I still enjoyed the crunchy crust and stringy cheese goodness that lingered as I took my first bite. Next time I'll probably just get plain cheese. Also, I love that they have parmesan, oregano, red pepper flakes, AND garlic powder! So many pizza places don't have all four of these condiments in the DMV! I got there around 11:30am; just before the lunch crowd of what appeared to be mostly teenagers and a few construction workers. The location has plenty of space for a large groups and bar height seating to individuals. There's even outdoor seating So I'm sure this place is busy during the summer, especially with the movie theater right next door.

The toppings are fresh, I can't abide canned mushrooms on a pizza, it ruins it and they obviously know better here. The sausage topping is perfect and precooked so it doesn't leave grease all over the pizza. Their subs are fresh and delicious, as well as everything else I've eaten there. I've been going to this restaurant for over 30 years and it's always consistently delicious. I've tried and loved nearly everything on the menu, but it's the absolutely amazing pizza that keeps me coming back year after year.

Pizza is pretty solid and has good ratios. The two slices and a drink for 5.50 is a great deal too. Subs and calzonnes are also tasty. A go to spot for me since I moved to Rockville.
Great pizza and pasta.  Some days better than others but I love their Stromboli's.

This place a is huge with the business lunch crowd, but we often hit it for dinner. Their pizza is excellent when you are taking a bite of everything. This is hard to explain, you see, their dough kinda sucks by itself,  so when you eat the crust, it is super bland, but when you take a bite of the pie the combination of cheese, sauce, and dough together is great, spot on. Funny thing about that bland crust. We end up with a tray empty of pizza with just the crusts there. Another hit is their antipasto salad. So good with meats and cheese and their homemade Italian dressing knocks it out of the park. This salad is a fantastic lunch BTW.
The best NY style pizza in  Rockville
Great place today meet for after run at a local school.

It was a busy Friday night. This resteraunt seems to draw a crowd for the theatre is nearby.  Despite the crowd the service was prompt.  The pizza was exactly what i ordered.  Well prepared and tasty.
Great place to eat!! Only 4 stars because the service could be a little more friendly!
Really good reasonably priced Pizza from a good Pittsburgh family.
Awesome pizza great staff steak and cheese one the best on the east coast
Pizza is ok and the prices are outrageous.
Best pizza and sins in Rockville!!
On time. Delicious. Courteous. Completed custom order accurately. Overheard staff dealing with a difficult customer in a professional manner. Efficient.
Great price's and really good pizza. I hope the Lightning take care of the Penguins for us! GO CAPS!!!
Incredible fast service, served with a smile great atmosphere awesome prices for great food.  Also great deal if you want to see a movie buy your tickets at discounted price.

What happened , we used to order pizza twice a month , but lately the pizza wasn't the same as before . I ordered 2 pizzas yesterday , one pepperoni and one half Hawaiian and half white pizza ,.... Terrible !,also chicken wings (the worst in the area) and the calmari too dry (I put it in the trash)... Good luck ! Luis

I have been eating this pizza since I was a little girl and it's still my absolute favorite pizza. And if I'm not eating the pizza, then I'm eating the steak and cheese with curly fries amazing! Not only is the food good but the people that work there are great. Love this place, can't beat the prices!
One of my favorite places for thin crispy pizza. Great prices <3
What someone else said: best pizza in the area.
Great price and portion. Perfect for jury service lunch! 6" philly w fries and drink under $9! Busy but efficient @lunch time waited 10 min for food.
Great pizza and enormous servings of sides. Really friendly environment and service. Only minor flaws are parking and Pittsburgh stuff.
This place has the best food.  Great crusty pizza.
Two words - comfort food!
We absolutely LOVE the pizza and everything there.  Keep the Pittsburgh stuff.
Good food, good prices and I love that they have beer and movie deals. However, this is Maryland. Get the Steelers trash off your wall. Baltimore is 30 minutes away
7 stars. Pepperoni pizza is the best In Rockville.
Really good calzones, meatball or steak subs.  Family run.  "Atmosphere" needs work.
My mom picked up a pie. When she got home the pie was brunt.  I like the pizza but the crust is doughie(middle). And taste less.
Careful ordering a slice of pizza during dinner it can take a while. Took me almost 15 min to get my slice. But the slice was delicious when I finally got it.

This is the go-to place for my wife and I when we go see a movie at the Regal right next door.  The $5 everyday pizza special can not be beat, and then the half price movie ticket purchase as well makes it even better.  I only rated the Decor as good because I am a Green Bay Packer fan and the place is covered in Pittsburg Steeler colors and flags.  Keep up the great service!

The best pizza in the area (greasy, delicious new york style.) They have been in the area for over 20 years and the same family is running the place as it was when this was next to Peoples in the OLD Rockville Town Square. They may be Steeler's fans, but with pizza dough this good I couldn't care less. To eat-in is a little cramped but I've never had an instance where I couldn't find a table, there's also outdoor seating for good weather. The 2-slices-and-a-soda lunch special for 5 bucks is a steal in this day and age and if you order a whole pie, the cheese and toppings are double what you'd get on individual slices. It may be expensive ($17 for a large) but it is absolutely worth it, and extremely filling.

If you're going to go to the movies, this isn't a bad place to eat, and you can get discounted tickets.  The pizza is about what you'd expect for NY-style pizza away from NYC, but isn't bad for the "grease taco" that New Yorkers seem to go nuts over.  What I don't understand is all of the Pittsburgh Steelers decor in what is a NY-style pizza joint...

Best pizza I have had in Maryland to date.  I swear to god, it's just like Mieno's in Pittsburgh (My favorite from when I lived in PA.).  My only gripe is the price.. but it's worth it.  *edit: I just read the below review calling it "Pittsburgh style" pizza.  I didn't know Pittsburgh had a style till now.
